50|$|In the {{original}} case (1966) {{the court did}} not raise the issue as to whether <b>the</b> <b>death</b> <b>penalty</b> <b>was</b> unconstitutional. In <b>the</b> second hearing, which also took place in 1968, the court did raise the issue but decided that <b>the</b> <b>death</b> <b>penalty</b> <b>was</b> neither cruel nor unusual. However, in view of Witherspoon, the court found that <b>the</b> defendants <b>death</b> sentence was unconstitutionally decided. In this third hearing, the court changed its mind and decided <b>the</b> <b>death</b> <b>penalty</b> <b>was</b> cruel or unusual.|$|R
